Here's another great example of a designer putting in the time to actually learn the basics of development.

> I always had ideas I wanted to bring to life, but I didn’t have the money to hire a developer, or know how to build them out myself. I’ve always loved the idea of taking a concept of mine from design, to front-end code, to back-end all myself.

He also went above and beyond. He didn't only learn Rails for himself, but as a challenge, he decided to record 12 video tutorials building a full app each time.

It might be a good place to start if you want to start learning.